source.name: Rent Affordability Gap by Neighborhood, San Francisco, CA
source.description: The data illustrate the number of minimum wage jobs that would be required to afford a two-bedroom rental unit at fair market rent value in San Francisco, as well as the gap between the median neighborhood household income and the estimated household income needed to afford a two bedroom unit at fair market rental value in that neighborhood.
